cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving convolutional neural networks (CNNs) by introducing a new adaptive filter model that allows variable scale and orientation. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks such as image classification and object recognition, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also discusses the use of back propagation for learning the scale and orientation parameters of filters, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper introduces a new method for creating filters using a differentiable function as an envelope, which could be relevant to researchers working on different types of neural networks (cs.NE) or signal processing (cs.MM).
